<item>
            <title>[TIKA-116] Streaming parser for OpenDocument files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-116</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current OpenOfficeParser first reads the entire meta.xml and content.xml files from the given OpenDocument zip into memory, then parses the in-memory files to DOM trees, merges the trees, and finally evaluates a number of XPath expressions against the resulting DOM tree to extract metadata and document content. All this requires quite a bit of memory and multiple passes over the document.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be better if the document could be streamed directly through zip and sax parsers without keeping a full copy of the document in memory or doing multiple passes over the document.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
